{p} {p}
{bold}Some finer more points of the AMIGA computer{nobold}
{p} {p}
1. When adding older CISC chips we can "patch " them together or Risc
several CISC chips together for a faster betterAMIGA.
{p} {p}
2. When we add a more powerful CPU i.e. 32bit to 64bit the AMIGA becomes
faster in all areas and the AMIGA is automatically a 64bit system
likewise for anything else as well as software.
{p} {p}
3. The OS (operating System ) can multitask in only 256k and the OS only
takes up 6megs of hardrive space.
{p} {p}
4. Real-time Multitasking is when you are able to do 2 or more things
with as little as ram possible but yet operate fast and efficently as
possible. I.E... format the floppy, get on the internet and download
several files at once, and also upload several files at once, and then
go on and do your wordprocessing while making an image in the
background(rendering).
