{p} {p}
Way back in 1995 when Gateway was advertising the Destination computer
and touting its capabilities. I called Gateway and got ahold of Jim
Collas (now President of AMIGA then Vice President of Gateway) and
TedWaite , President of Gateway. I told them that I represented AMIGA
yeah but so does anybody that owns one. The point is that I said that
you could be sued and to say that you were the first When the AMIGA is
the first Destination style computer. It has now become liable and for
you to claim as such so you need to buy out AMIGA , and I said that with
a major emphasis on buyout. No sooner had I said that then the
destination commercial that was on was cut off and a stupid old
commercial was put on. Since that time there has been no real
Destination commercials and AMIGA was bought out from GATEWAY with the
express purpose of updating to the AMIGA platform. Hence the two year
upgrade policy they now advertise. Soon the Look and feel will be
different.That will be because there is an AMIGA inside no Intel nor any
other PC piece of crap.
